# Org-control / Project context

This project (**winkslawncare**) uses org-control (org skills only; no MCP required). Org preferences (strictness, ask_before) are used by org skills; use **org-preferences** to read or update them.

**Stack / context:** Stack TBD; add package.json or README when the project is initialized.

**Conventions:** Add README or docs for conventions when available.

- When planning or enforcing policy, use **org-orchestrator** and **org-preferences**.
- When the user's intent is unclear, use **org-receptionist** to route.
- For review, docs, QA, risk, content, SEO, use the corresponding org skill (org-senior-dev, org-docs-team, org-qa-team, org-feedback-loop, org-architecture-steward, org-risk-assessor, org-content-strategist, org-content-creator, org-tailwind-reviewer, org-seo-reviewer, component-philosophy).
- For setting up another project's rules in this workspace, use **org-project-setup**.
